article.headline: Brown 73, Dartmouth 70 (2OT)
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Keenan Jeppesen scored a career-high 25 points to lead Brown to a 73-70 double overtime win over Dartmouth on Friday night. The Bears (5-10, 1-1 Ivy League) outscored the Big Green in the second overtime 9-6. Marcus Becker gave the Bears the lead for good, 72-70, with a free throw with 18.5 seconds remaining. Dartmouth overcame an early first-half deficit with a 10-0 run. But the Bears, who went 5:58 without a field goal, chipped away and tied the game at 25-25 on Luke Ruscoe's jumper with 2:29 remaining in the half, then took a 27-25 halftime lead. Jeppesen scored 17 in the second half. Scott Friske finished with 12 points for the Bears while Damon Huffman added 10. Mike Lang led Dartmouth (2-13, 0-2) with 21 points, including five 3-pointers. Leon Pattman had 12. Dartmouth's Calvin Arnold tied the game at 64-64 with a long jumper in the first overtime.
